com.isoterik.mgdx.ai.fsm.conditions

Class NumericCompoundCondition<T extends java.lang.Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.isoterik.mgdx.ai.fsm.conditions.CompoundCondition
      • com.isoterik.mgdx.ai.fsm.conditions.NumericCompoundCondition<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of number to compare. Currently supports precision to as high as Float precision.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICondition

    public class NumericCompoundCondition<T extends java.lang.Number>
extends CompoundCondition
    A condition that delegates to other conditions to create a complex condition. This condition is capable of comparing Numbers directly. This condition initially delegates to EqualsCondition on construction, subsequent conditions are compounded to yield a final condition.
    See Also:
    CompoundCondition
